2.name: Inspired
2.tip_text: Bruenor does more damage if he's adjacent to more Champions. Place him next to as many Champions as you can.

4.name: Rally
4.tip_text: Bruenor increases the damage of Champions in the same column as him. Place him in the same column as your most damaging Champions.

24.name: Crusader's Mantle
24.tip_text: Celeste increases the damage of adjacent Champions. Place her next to your most damaging Champions.

26.name: Mass Cure Wounds
26.tip_text: Celeste heals everyone in the column in front of her. Place her behind your front-most Champions to keep them alive longer.

38.name: Aura of Courage
38.tip_text: Nayeli increases the damage of Champions in the column behind hers. Place her in front of your most damaging Champions.

40.name: Aura of Protection
40.tip_text: Nayeli increases your formation's damage for each enemy attacking her. Place her at the front of your formation to take advantage of this.

52.name: Master of Disguise
52.tip_text: Jarlaxle increases his own damage when he is adjacent to Good or Neutral Champions.

2188.name: Master of Piracy
2188.tip_text: Jarlaxle increases your gold find based on the number of Drow or Rogue Champions in your formation.

71.name: Bardic Inspiration
71.tip_text: Calliope inspires those in front of her to do more damage. Place her behind your most damaging Champions.

72.name: Song of Protection
72.tip_text: Calliope protects those near her when they are damaged. Place her within two slots of your front-line to ensure her song reaches them.

90.name: Bond: Humans
90.tip_text: Asharra has formed a bond of friendship with your Human champions. Focus on having those champions as your main damage dealers.

91.name: Bond: Dwarves and Elves
91.tip_text: Asharra has formed a bond of friendship with your Dwarf and Elf champions (including Drow). Focus on having those champions as your main damage dealers.

92.name: Bond: Potpourri
92.tip_text: Asharra has formed a bond of friendship with your Aarakocra, Dragonborn, Firbolg, Lizardfolk, Minotaur, Tiefling, and Tortle champions. Focus on having those champions as your main damage dealers.

976.tip_text: Asharra has formed a bond of friendship with your Aasimar, Genasi, Gith, Saurial, Tabaxi , Warforged, and Yuan-ti champions. Focus on having those champions as your main damage dealers.

977.name: Bond: Short-folk
977.tip_text: Asharra has formed a bond of friendship with your Gnome, Goblin, Halfling, and Kobold champions. Focus on having those champions as your main damage dealers.

108.tip_text: Minsc has a history with Humanoid enemies, so with his direction the party does additional damage to any Humanoids.

2194.name: Surge of Power
2194.tip_text: Delina's damage fluctuates over time, waxing and waning as she blasts enemies relentlessly with her magic.

2195.name: Spell Bombardment
2195.tip_text: Delina deals additional damage if she's further back in the formation. Put her near the back to maximize the effect!

139.name: Dark Luck
139.tip_text: Enemies that Makos lands the killing blow on drop additional gold.

140.name: Dark Blessing
140.tip_text: Champions that are not adjacent to Makos deal additional damage. Make sure he's not adjacent to other damage dealers to increase their damage.

145.name: Moonbeam
145.tip_text: Tyril increases your party's damage, but the increase is reduced by each Champion next to him. Keep him on his own to maximize the benefit.

146.name: Wild Shape
146.tip_text: Tyril can be an excellent tank. Keep him at the front of your formation to soak up damage.

150.name: Druidic Healing
150.tip_text: Tyril heals those next to him. Place him next to your front-line tanks to help keep them alive longer.

151.name: Wild Resilience
151.tip_text: Tyril reduces damage done to himself by a certain amount each hit. Place him at the front of your formation to protect your other Champions.

238.name: Frontline Fighter
238.tip_text: Jamilah's damage is increased when she's near tanks. Put her near the front of your formation to take advantage of this.

2198.name: Berserker Confidence
2198.tip_text: Jamilah's damage is increased dramatically when she has a temporary hit point shield on her. Pair her with Champions that shield!

242.name: Rage of the Dragonborn
242.tip_text: Arkhan attacks more ferociously when there are more enemies attacking him. Place him in your front line!

243.name: Bulk Up
243.tip_text: Arkhan increases the affect of formation abilities targeting him. Buff him up to take advantage of this effect!

244.name: Usurped Power
244.tip_text: Arkhan is also affected by some formation abilities affecting champions adjacent to him. Build your formation accordingly.

384.name: Spare Dagger
384.tip_text: Hitch somehow always has a spare dagger up his sleeve, and will toss it at a random enemy before he attacks.

390.name: Natural Performer
390.tip_text: Hitch increases the damage of Champions with high Charisma scores. Use Champions with high scores to increase their damage.

410.name: Golden Palm
410.tip_text: Enemies killed by Champions adjacent to Stoki drop bonus gold based on the number of active Marks of Ki.

411.name: Ki Strike
411.tip_text: Stoki leaves a Mark of Ki on enemies she attacks, and then buffs the formation based on the number of active Marks of Ki.

444.name: Eldritch Strike
444.tip_text: Enemies that Krond attacks multiple times take extra damage from his Cantrips.

445.name: Cantrip: Thunderclap
445.tip_text: Krond casts the Thunderclap cantrip when he attacks, dealing AOE damage to all nearby enemies.

446.name: Cantrip: Shocking Grasp
446.tip_text: Krond casts the Shocking Grasp cantrip when he attacks, dealing additional damage to his primary target.

447.name: Cantrip: Fire Bolt
447.tip_text: Krond casts the Fire Bolt cantrip when he attacks, dealing additional damage to three random enemies.

549.name: Grandmotherly Love
549.tip_text: Gromma increases the damage of other champions in the formation based on their age; the younger they are, the greater the buff.

551.tip_text: Gromma focuses on protecting those in the formation by reducing damage taken from ranged attackers.

552.tip_text: Gromma focuses on supporting those in the formation by reducing the effectiveness of enemies she hits.

553.tip_text: Gromma focuses on damaging the formation's enemies by using a powerful ranged spell to attack.

596.name: Skill Empowerment
596.tip_text: Dhadius's Skill Empowerment spell affects all Champions within 2 formation slots of himself. Place intelligent Champions near Dhadius to make use of his blunder.

597.name: Practice Makes Perfect
597.tip_text: Dhadius' Chromatic Orb attack does more and more damage the more times he casts the same element in a row. Can you get lucky!?

633.name: Twinkle
633.tip_text: When Drizzt attacks a target Guenhwyvar has attacked, his twin scimitars cause additional effects.

2783.name: Guenhwyvar
2783.tip_text: Drizzt regularily summons his panther companion, Guenhwyvar, to aid in battle with vicious bleed attacks.

10684.name: Blessed Hammer
10684.tip_text: Barrowin causes Champions behind her to do additional damage based on the number of Champions in the formation with equal or higher attack speed than her.

10686.name: Healing Word
10686.tip_text: Barrowin heals Champions in the same column as her. Place her in a column that takes a lot of damage!

695.name: Ruby Encouragement
695.tip_text: Regis increases the damage of Champions in the column in front of him. Place him directly behind your best damage dealers!

696.name: Ruby Encouragement
696.tip_text: Regis increases the damage of Champions in the column right behind him. Place him directly in front of your best damage dealers!

697.name: Ruby Weakness
697.tip_text: Regis increases the damage taken by monsters from ranged attacks. Make sure your best damage dealers attack with ranged damage!

698.name: Ruby Weakness
698.tip_text: Regis increases the damage taken by monsters from melee attacks. Make sure your best damage dealers attack with melee damage!

699.name: Ruby Weakness
699.tip_text: Regis increases the damage taken by monsters from magic attacks. Make sure your best damage dealers attack with magic damage!

10774.name: Song of Battle
10774.tip_text: Birdsong buffs Champions within two slots of herself. Use her as your main DPS, or keep your main DPS nearby.

10775.name: Chorus of the Lost
10775.tip_text: Birdsong works best when she's getting buffed by unaffiliated Champions.

848.name: Hunter's Pack
848.tip_text: Zorbu increases the damage of himself and adjacent Champions with high DEX scores. Place high DEX Champions next to Zorbu.

857.name: Lifelong Enemies
857.tip_text: Zorbu gains a damage bonus for each enemy he kills of certain types. These bonuses persist through resets.

870.name: Haunted
870.tip_text: Strix increases your party's damage for each ally who has been killed.

871.name: Poor Hygiene
871.tip_text: Strix causes enemies that approach your party to take additional damage.

902.name: Ki Master
902.tip_text: Nrakk gains Ki Points when attacking, making him attack faster and do more damage.

912.name: Githzerai Focus
912.tip_text: Nrakk buffs the abilities of wise Champions next to him. Construct your formation take advantage of this gift!

1034.name: Critical Hit
1034.tip_text: Catti-brie's damage comes through her Critical Hits, which she can share with others through her ultimate attack.

1035.name: Mark for Death
1035.tip_text: Enemies damaged by Catti-brie take additional damage from everyone and can be stunned after enough hits.

1075.name: Lathander's Grace
1075.tip_text: Evelyn is a tanking champion focused on taking the hit for the team. Place her at the front of the formation.

1076.name: Divine Prayer
1076.tip_text: Evelyn buffs everyone behind her based on recent actions taken by or against her.

1110.name: Extra Attacks
1110.tip_text: Binwin can attack multiple times per attack, doing more damage with each attack. He excels against large groups of durable enemies.

1111.name: Crash and Smash
1111.tip_text: Binwin deals double damage against armored and hits-based enemies.

1148.name: Story of Doom
1148.tip_text: Deekin tells a story to those adjacent to him, increasing their damage the longer he isn't distracted. Place him next to your highest damage dealers!

1151.name: Troubadour Troupe
1151.tip_text: Deekin is more effective with multiple bards in the formation. Use more bards to increase your party's damage!

1192.name: Distraction
1192.tip_text: Xander causes some enemies he kills (or misses) to count for extra quest progress.

1193.name: Streetwise
1193.tip_text: Xander buffs the damage of those behind him. Place him in front of your best damage dealers.

1232.name: Curse of Lycanthropy
1232.tip_text: Azaka transforms into a weretiger after several hits. Her damage increases while she's a weretiger.

1233.name: Guiding Hand
1233.tip_text: Azaka increases your gold found; this bonus is reduced when she's in weretiger form.

1241.name: Monsters are People Too!
1241.tip_text: Ishi's damage is increased by having non-humans in the formation. Stack your formation with other races to buff her!

1242.name: Let's Find Some Treasure
1242.tip_text: Ishi increases the party's gold find when she's next to non-humans. Place her intelligently to capitalize on this!

1509.name: Moradin's Will
1509.tip_text: Wulfgar increases the damage of the Companions of the Hall when he's under attack, making him an ideal tank for a Companions-based formation.

1510.name: Clangeddin's Will
1510.tip_text: Wulfgar stuns enemies with his base attack, and buffs the formation based on the enemies that are stunned.

1548.name: Chosen of Asmodeus
1548.tip_text: Farideh's Hellish Rebuke triggers when enemies hit allies near her. Position her near your tanking Champions to take advantage of this.

1549.name: Pact Family
1549.tip_text: Farideh's damage is increased by the number of tieflings in the formation. Load up your formation with tieflings to really power her up!

1592.name: Aura of Vitality
1592.tip_text: Donaar heals the most damaged members of your formation, regardless of where they are in relation to him.

1593.name: Lead By Example
1593.tip_text: Donaar buffs Champions in the same column and columns behind him. Place him near the front of your formation to gain the biggest benefit.

1656.name: Enthralling Performance
1656.tip_text: Vlahnya buffs those ahead of her in the formation. Place her far enough back in your formation to buff your hardest hitters.

1657.name: Witch Slap
1657.tip_text: Vlahnya briefly stuns enemies that she attacks.

1895.name: Hex
1895.tip_text: Warden Hexes all enemies that they attack, causing them to take extra damage.

1898.name: Relentless Hex
1898.tip_text: Hex can stack up to 4 times. The more Warden attacks, the more damage enemies take.

9742.name: Spiritual Weapon
9742.tip_text: Nerys's Spiritual Weapon deals bonus damage when it attacks.

9743.name: War Healing
9743.tip_text: Nerys heals Champions in a column whenever her Spiritual weapon attacks.

1981.name: Hoardsperson
1981.tip_text: K'thriss collects some of the formation's earnings, but don't fret -- he uses it to summon a helpful demon!

1982.name: Unseen Encouragement
1982.tip_text: K'thriss buffs those farthest from him in the formation. He can be tricky to position, but is a powerful buffer!

2035.name: Magical Secrets
2035.tip_text: Paultin increases the damage of everyone not adjacent to him, based on the number of Champions that ARE adjacent to him!

2108.name: Aura of Infamy
2108.tip_text: Black Viper is buffed more effectively by Bards, Rogues, and eventually Rangers and Warlocks. Build a formation with those classes to make the best use of her.

2110.name: Jewel Thief
2110.tip_text: Black Viper powers up over time by collecting Red Gems. Red Gems have both a permanent effect that persists between runs and a damage bonus that applies to the current run.

2149.name: Sassy
2149.tip_text: Rosie's damage is increased by having Champions in the formation who are younger than she is. Stack that formation!

2150.name: Deflect Missiles
2150.tip_text: Rosie can deflect ranged/magic attacks back at ranged attackers, as long as she's close to the Champion being attacked.

8779.name: Storm Aura
8779.tip_text: Aila periodically Primes enemies with her lightning aura, increasing the damage they take from all Champions.

8780.name: Storm Soul
8780.tip_text: Aila's attacks cause Primed enemies to become Electrified, further increasing the damage they take from all Champions.

10677.name: Heroic Sacrifice
10677.tip_text: Spurt's ultimate causes him to temporarily sacrifice himself, increasing the effects of his other abilities.

10679.name: Wa-spiration
10679.tip_text: Spurt's attacks grant him the inspiration he needs to create new and interesting buffs for the party.

8767.name: Prayer of Healing
8767.tip_text: Qillek heals allies that are not adjacent to him.

8768.name: Bless
8768.tip_text: Qillek increases the damage of adjacent allies based on how he is positioned in the formation.

2323.name: Lizardfolk Tactics
2323.tip_text: Korth applies a debuff to enemies he attacks that decreases the base attack cooldown of anyone who attacks them.

2324.name: Calculated
2324.tip_text: Korth buffs the formation based on the number of Champions who have attacked his marked enemies recently.

2386.name: Documancer
2386.tip_text: Walnut increases the damage of some Champions in the formation for each enemy killed.

2388.name: Wolfnut
2388.tip_text: Walnut shapeshifts into a wolf when she is under attack, gaining a shield and becoming tankier.

9727.name: Agile Allies
9727.tip_text: Shandie buffs Champions within two slots of herself based on the DEX scores of adjacent allies.

9728.name: Dash
9728.tip_text: Shandie makes your formation move faster when it's not under attack. Use her to reach your wall faster!

2888.name: Fan Club
2888.tip_text: Jim's damage is increased based on the number of Champions in the columns in front of and behind him.

2890.name: Magic {magic}#CCC {magic}#888 {magic}#444
2890.tip_text: Jim increases the damage of all magical Champions (including himself) based on the number of magical Champions in the formation.

2892.name: Is There An Echo In Here?
2892.specialization_name: Is There An Echo In Here?

10657.name: Embodiment of the Law
10657.tip_text: Turiel buffs Champions in the columns behind him, based on how far back they are.

10660.name: Unflinching Hatred
10660.tip_text: Turiel hates fiends with a fiery passion and buffs the formation even more when fighting fiends.

3030.name: Count 'Em Off
3030.tip_text: Pwent increases the damage of the party each time an enemy he has attacked is killed.

3033.name: Gutbuster Recruits
3033.tip_text: Pwent increases the cooldown and damage of Champions near him. Place him next to a few Champions to get the biggest benefit from this.

3044.name: Mirror Image
3044.tip_text: Avren summons Mirror Images on random Champions, buffing them based on their roles.

3100.name: Seeing Double
3100.tip_text: Avren buffs the party based on how many buffs his Mirror Images are providing.

8761.name: Guardian of Solwynn
8761.tip_text: Sentry buffs those near her, so make sure your main DPS is nearby.

8863.name: Create Echo
8863.tip_text: Sentry's companion, Echo, buffs the party based on whether or not Sentry has been attacked recently.

3267.name: Observance
3267.tip_text: Artemis observes and duplicates a portion of formational abilities affecting other DPS Champions in the formation. You'll need a unique formation to take advantage of this.

3268.name: Jeweled Power
3268.tip_text: Artemis' power increases over time as he gets kills; this power gets unleashed randomly when he attacks.

3326.name: Paid Up Front
3326.tip_text: Mrgn collects a portion of the gold dropped by monsters but then buffs the formation partially based on the gold collected.

3327.name: Friends In Wealth
3327.tip_text: Mrgn loves adventuring with Gold Finding Champions (because who doesn't).

3431.name: Summon Imps
3431.tip_text: Havilar summons and sacrifices her Imps using her ultimate ability. Use it at the right time to gain superior benefits!

3432.name: Leadership Summit
3432.tip_text: Havilar is a tank who increases the damage of those in the two columns behind her.

3440.name: Halo of Spores
3440.tip_text: Sisaspia infects enemies as they approach, causing them to take additional damage over time from each attack.

3441.name: Symbiotic Infection
3441.tip_text: Sisaspia uses the spores she has in reserve to buff nearby Champions.

3450.name: Steelbones
3450.tip_text: Briv stores power whenever he takes damage and uses it to buff the party and Sprint forward.

3453.name: Healing Phlo
3453.tip_text: Briv's pet flumph, Phlo, tracks the damage that Briv takes and then heals the party using the tracked amount.

3510.name: Melf's Augmented Support Spell
3510.tip_text: Melf creates a customized support spell to buff the formation partially based on the Champions placed into it.

3511.name: Melf's Speedy Supplement
3511.tip_text: Melf provides a speed boosting ability, potentially switching it up every 50 areas to keep things fresh.

9629.name: From The Shadows
9629.tip_text: Krydle increase the damage of champions in the two rearmost columns in the formation.

9631.name: Evasion
9631.tip_text: Krydle can evade attacks, completely negating their effect.

9710.name: Fierce Hunter
9710.tip_text: Jaheira is a fierce hunter of certain creatures. Killing those enemies buff her other abilities.

9717.name: Class Act - Baldur's Gate
9717.tip_text: Jaheira supports certain classes. Make sure your main DPS Champion is a supported class!

8747.name: Curiosity
8747.tip_text: Nova is intrinsically curious about the world around her. She increases the damage done to creatures the longer they are alive.

8748.name: The Crew
8748.tip_text: Nova increases the damage of all nearby Champions based on the sum of their levels.

4038.name: Luck of Yondalla
4038.tip_text: Freely and all his allies have the Luck of Yondalla backing them up, afflicting enemies with random debuffs.

4039.name: Adventurous Tale
4039.tip_text: Freely recounts the party's adventures, increasing your divine favor upon reset.

4175.name: Long Rest
4175.tip_text: Beadle & Grimm get more powerful the longer they are inactive. Hold off using their ultimate for a while to get a big burst of power!

4180.name: Tag Team
4180.tip_text: Beadle & Grimm share a slot and swap with eachother when their ultimate is used.

4108.name: Shadow Council
4108.tip_text: Omin buffs others in the formation; position him so that he always buffs your main damage dealers.

4109.name: Champion of Tymora
4109.tip_text: Omin recruits others in the formation to be Champions of Tymora. If you play your cards right, you can sometimes spread this to your entire formation.

4475.name: Fury of the Small
4475.tip_text: Lazaapz works best with small races (dwarves, goblins, gnomes, halflings, and kobolds). The more the merrier.

4476.name: Power Armor
4476.tip_text: Lazaapz powers up her armor when she's not under attack and then unleashes it when she is.

3272.name: Shen-state
3272.tip_text: Dragonbait increases the damage of nearby Champions. The range can be extended with clever formations.

3274.name: Scent: Roasted Vegetables
3274.tip_text: Dragonbait is a defensive tank, and will increase the damage of all Champions when he comes under attack.

4346.name: Spellcaster School
4346.tip_text: Ulkoria's abilities gets stronger when there are more spellcasters in the formation.

4348.name: Defender of Waterdeep
4348.tip_text: Ulkoria is at home in the streets and alleys of Waterdeep and increases everyone's damage when you start adventures there.

4488.tip_text: Torogar gains Zealot stacks whenever he or an adjacent Champion kill an enemy; Zealot stacks empower Torogar and his allies

4491.name: Blood Rage
4491.tip_text: Torogar periodically enters a Blood Rage, greatly empowering his abilities.

4494.name: Training Montage
4494.tip_text: Ezmerelda debuffs enemies as they spawn and as she strikes them, increasing the damage done by those in her own column.

4496.name: Threat Tracking
4496.tip_text: Ezmerelda increases her power as you kill Undead enemies. The enemy type can be changed via specialization.

4565.name: Have You Met My Friends
4565.tip_text: Penelope causes enemies she hits but doesn't kill to take additional damage from other Champions.

4566.name: Chwinga Mask
4566.tip_text: When the formation comes under attack Penelope buffs the formation based on those Champions around her.

8727.name: Arcane Chromat - Acid
8727.tip_text: Lucius deals extra damage to enemies the more times he attacks them.

8728.name: Arcane Chromat - Cold
8728.tip_text: Lucius deals extra damage to slowed, stunned, and rooted enemies.

4746.name: Cause For Celebration
4746.tip_text: Champions immediately in front or behind Baeloth kill enemies in an explosion of confetti that can damage nearby enemies.

4748.name: Generous Djinn
4748.tip_text: Champions revived by Najim provide a large buff which lasts until they are killed again.

4762.name: Spot Weakness
4762.tip_text: Talin observes weaknesses of enemies and whispers them to nearby Champions increasing their damage.

4763.name: Scatter Tacks
4763.tip_text: Talin scatters tacks behind him after attacking, slowing enemies that walk in that area.

10648.name: Teamwork
10648.tip_text: Hew Maan provides different buffs depending on their proximity to the front of the formation.

10649.name: Hello, Fellow Humans
10649.tip_text: Hew Maan buffs their abilities based on the number of "other" humans in the formation.

10653.name: Did We Say Humans? We Meant...
10653.specialization_name: Did We Say Humans? We Meant...

4906.name: Flaming Wings
4906.tip_text: When Orisha uses her ultimate her Wings burst aflame, increasing damage, kills further increase damage but make the wings burn out more quickly.

4907.name: Bardic Connection
4907.tip_text: Orisha has a strong connection with Vlahnya, they strongly buff each others abilities.

5377.name: Portent
5377.tip_text: Every 30 seconds, Alyndra peers into the future of the formation, increasing the damage of random adjacent Champions.

5379.name: Brows of Judgement
5379.tip_text: Griff judges enemies as they spawn increasing the effect of Portent per judged enemy.

5572.name: Lesser Restoration
5572.tip_text: Orkira heals non-adjacent Champions who are damaged.

5573.name: Elemental Fire
5573.tip_text: Orkira leaves a stacking debuff and DoT on enemies she damages.

5647.name: A Celestial Puzzle
5647.tip_text: Shaka solves a random puzzle on each adventure, buffing all Champions

5648.name: Celestial Resistance
5648.tip_text: Shaka grants temporary hit points to all Champions as they change areas.

5636.name: Grumpy
5636.tip_text: Mehen buffs Champions in his column and all columns in front of him based on a number of events

5638.name: Found Family
5638.tip_text: Mehen grants bonus gold for every Tiefling in the formation.

5780.name: Divine Sense
5780.tip_text: Selise offers different bonus effects and different ways to buff the champions in the columns behind her in her 4 different stances.

5783.name: Thunderous Smite
5783.tip_text: When Selise moves from her Last Resort Stance to her Aggressive stance, she unleashes a powerful Thunderous Smite on multiple enemies

5980.name: Rallying Cry
5980.tip_text: Sergeant Knox buffs the champions behind him, based on the number of positional formation abilities affecting them

5981.name: Blessed By Selne
5981.tip_text: Sergeant Knox is at his best when paired with Celeste and Makos

5990.name: The Deck of Many Things
5990.tip_text: Every 100 areas Ellywick pulls a different card from the Deck of Many Things, modyfing the ability on which she is increasing her bonus.

5991.name: Powerful Following
5991.tip_text: Ellywick buffs the damage of Champions in the column behind her, this bonus is increased by Knight stacks.

6068.name: Glee
6068.tip_text: Prudence delights in killing her enemies, each kill increases her damage (to a max).

6069.name: Delight
6069.tip_text: Good Champions in the formation further increase her damage bonus.

6129.name: Pirate's Code
6129.tip_text: Corazn increases the damage of all Neutral (Good/Evil axis) Champions in the formation

6130.name: Grease
6130.tip_text: Corazn drops Grease puddles when he attacks, these impede all enemies who walk through them

5457.name: Echoes of Zariel
5457.tip_text: The gaze of Zariel passes over champions, the more it visits prior to Reya the higher the bonus to her buffs.

5458.name: Celestial Champion
5458.tip_text: Reya buffs Good and Lawful Champions more than any other.

6139.name: Fighter
6139.tip_text: When the fighter is active and enemies are attacking the NERDS buff the Champions behind them.

6140.name: Ranger
6140.tip_text: Enemies attacked by the NERDS while the ranger is active take more damage from other champions too.

6834.name: Perfect Imitation
6834.tip_text: While Xerophon is transformed, they do not attack; however, all Champions deal more damage.

6835.name: Adaptable
6835.tip_text: Xerophon causes all Champions to deal more damage, this is buffed by the number of Champion ability scores that do NOT match their specialization choices.

6216.name: Paint Them Red
6216.tip_text: D'hani paints enemies she attacks, this causes them to take extra damage based on the number of paint strokes she can see.

6218.name: Way of the Brush
6218.tip_text: D'hani remembers all the enemies she has ever painted, this strengthens her attacks against all future enemies.

6350.name: Hype
6350.tip_text: Brig increases the damage of all Champions in the formation

6352.name: Inspired Bard
6352.tip_text: Brig increases his damage buff for adjacent champions who deal more damage than him

6905.name: Vampiric Gaze
6905.tip_text: Widdle's vampiric gaze boosts the damage of all adjacent Champions

6908.name: Only As Slow As The Fastest Link
6908.tip_text: Champions affected by Widdle's Vampiric gaze get the same (fastest) base attack cooldown.

6986.name: Blood Fury Tattoo
6986.tip_text: Each of Yorven's Ferocious Maul attacks makes the enemy take additional damage for 2 seconds

6988.name: Danger Sense
6988.tip_text: Champions adjacent to Yorven take less damage from attacks, and his damage is increased when they do

9782.name: Animate Dead
9782.tip_text: Viconia has a chance to animate dead enemies and turn them against their friends.

9783.name: Cure Medium Wounds
9783.tip_text: Viconia heals Champions that have been gravely injured.

7164.name: Rust For Hire
7164.tip_text: Rust increases gold find, the effect is greatly increased when he has his One Gold Piece

7165.name: Highest Bidder
7165.tip_text: Rust increases the damage of all Champions for each order of magnitude of the party Gold Find; further increased when holding his One Gold Piece

7177.name: A Good Example
7177.tip_text: Vi buffs Neutral Champions by the number of Good Champions surrounding them

7179.name: I'm Too Old For This #*&!
7179.tip_text: Vi gets bored if there aren't enough enemies to attack, her sass reduces the time between enemy waves

7182.name: A Nudge In The Right Direction
7182.specialization_name: A Nudge In The Right Direction

7300.name: Howl at the Moon
7300.tip_text: Desmond synergizes with the phases of the Moon. Increasing the base attack speed of Champions closer to the Full Moon.

7303.name: Lament the Lost
7303.tip_text: Desmond buffs all Champion damage based on the number of slots that are blocked by a dead champion or escort.

7382.name: Faithful Friend
7382.tip_text: Tatyana buffs the damage of a randomly chosen champion in the middle columns of the formation

7385.name: Find a Feast
7385.tip_text: If Tatyana has not been attacked recently she grabs some snacks and brings back some extra enemies to fight

7534.name: Frosty Friendship
7534.tip_text: Gazrick buffs all Champions in a unique snowflake formation

7536.name: Armor Ablation
7536.tip_text: Gazrick reduces the amount of damage required to destroy a section of armor from an armored enemy

7844.name: Patience, Young Ones!
7844.tip_text: Dungeon Master buffs the damage of all champions based on the number of Champions under 20 in the formation

7845.name: Words of Encouragement
7845.tip_text: Dungeon Master grants 50 Temporary Hit Points to everyone in the party everytime he chooses to join the formation for an area.

7849.name: Where Did He Go This Time?
7849.specialization_name: Where Did He Go This Time?

7856.name: Form Orderly Ranks
7856.tip_text: Nordom buffs all Champions in the column in front of him, this is increased based on the number of Lawful Champions in the formation.

7858.name: Modron Core Toolbox
7858.tip_text: Nordom increases the XP earned by active modron cores attached to the party he is in.

7993.name: A Neutral Party
7993.tip_text: Merilwen buffs the damage of all Neutral (Good/Evil axis) Champions

7995.name: Wild Shape
7995.tip_text: Merilwen transforms into a cat if there aren't enough enemies around to defeat, this speeds up the attack cooldown of adjacent Champions

8009.name: Who Am I?
8009.tip_text: Nahara does more damage for every adventure area she completes over all time.

8010.name: To Amuse or Avenge
8010.tip_text: Nahara allows champions to complete future areas more quickly when she is easily defeating enemies, and when she is not she starts to deal more damage.

8147.name: Socialite
8147.tip_text: Valentine duplicates positional formation abilities affecting her on DPS Champions. This happens after Artemis' Observation ability.

8639.name: Calculating Guidance
8639.tip_text: Voronika increases the damage of all Champions in the column in front of her.

8640.name: Search for the Crown
8640.tip_text: Voronika has three quests to complete, and she becomes much stronger when they are complete.

8739.name: Traveling Entertainer
8739.tip_text: Dob boosts the damage of all Champions NOT adjacent to him, keep him away from your DPS.

8741.name: Offshore Accounting
8741.tip_text: Sometimes when heading to a new area, Dob helpfully throws all your saved gold into a lake. Each time he does this his other abilities are buffed!

7518.name: Soul Gatherer
7518.tip_text: Blooshi gains Soul stacks for each enemy killed, buffing the champions in the two columns behind her.

7519.name: Spirit Carries On
7519.tip_text: Blooshi's powerful Spirit tanks for the formation when she dies, until the next boss is defeated

8872.name: Atone for the Past
8872.tip_text: Egbert buffs Champion damage based on the number of Lawful or Chaotic Champions in the formation, focus on one end of the axis to maximize this bonus.

8873.name: Lay On Hands
8873.tip_text: Egbert heals the most damage Champion after each attack based on the absolute value of Atonement Points

9351.name: Tokens of the Departed
9351.tip_text: Kent keeps a Soul Token from the highest level boss he helped defeat in each campaign.  These tokens buff the party.

9352.name: Remembering the Old Days
9352.tip_text: Each time Kent or his ghostly companions attack he gains Nostalgia making him deal even more damage until changing areas.

9603.name: Storm Sorcerer
9603.tip_text: Virgil buffs the Champions adjacent to him by increasing their damage and decreasing their attack cooldown.

9604.name: Weather Control
9604.tip_text: Virgil increases the damage of all Champions based on how many times the weather has changed.

9615.name: A Trained Killer
9615.tip_text: Every time warduke attacks or is damaged, he deals more damage on his next attack. This bonus resets when changing areas.

9617.name: Chaotic Inversion
9617.tip_text: Warduke inverts the targets of many positional formation abilities, opening up completely new formations.

9639.name: Optimism
9639.tip_text: Imoen buffs the champions adjacent to her.

9640.name: Perseverance
9640.tip_text: Imoen increases her buff any time a Favored Foe appears or is defeated.

9757.name: Mischievous, but Dangerous
9757.tip_text: Fen increases the damage of Champions in her column.

9760.name: Patron's Oath
9760.tip_text: Fen increases the amount of progress credited in Patron Challenges in the party she is in.

9770.name: Doomed in Darkon
9770.tip_text: Brother Uriah increases the damage of Champons in his column and the column behind.

9771.name: Ezra's Embrace
9771.tip_text: Brother Uriah heals all Champions within 2 slots of him.

9772.name: In the Grip of Azalin Rex

10611.name: Compatriots
10611.tip_text: Solaak increases the damage of ranged Champions based on the number of ranged Champions in the formation.

10613.name: Critical Mass
10613.tip_text: Solaak increases the effect of outgoing positional formation abilities of ranged champions.

10665.name: Mage of High Sorcery
10665.tip_text: Miria increases the damage of Champions adjacent to her, keep her next to your highest damage dealing champions.

10667.name: Zombie Bodyguards
10667.tip_text: Miria protects the formation by summoning Zombie Bodyguards to protect the frontmost Champions. She does not need to be in the front column to be effective.

10794.name: Inspiring Song
10794.tip_text: Antrius protects and buffs adjacent Champions.

10795.name: The Hardiest, Bardiest Bard
10795.tip_text: Inspiring Song is buffed based on the number of Champions affected by it. Use Charismatic champions to spread and buff it.

10800.name: The "A" In Chaotic Is For Antrius
10800.specialization_name: The "A" In Chaotic Is For Antrius

10887.name: Blazing Charisma
10887.tip_text: Nixie increases the damage of all Champions with 17+ Charisma including herself.

10888.name: Wild Magic Surge
10888.tip_text: Each time Nixie makes a normal attack, there is a high chance that a random wild magic event happens. Many are good, some are not.

11295.name: Freedom's Fury
11295.tip_text: Evandra buffs Neutral Champions on the Good / Evil axis. Try using Lawful and Chaotic Neutral Champions with her.

11296.name: Never Completely 'Armless
11296.tip_text: The first time Evandra would otherwise die in an area, she merely loses and arm and returns to full health.

11539.name: Evil Overlord
11539.tip_text: BBEG increases the damage of all Champions with an INT score of 12 or less.

11543.name: Railroad
11543.tip_text: BBEG reduces the next area quest requirements if you are completing areas quickly.
